om\": 2276, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"Long\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can melt down all the medals and cups I have and they would not be a plating on the 24-carat friendship I felt for Long at that moment.\\\"\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the medals\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2335}, {\"ngram\": \"cups\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"a plating\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2383}, {\"ngram\": \"the 24-carat friendship\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"Long\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2426}, {\"ngram\": \"that moment\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rankin says the two became \\\"comrades, became allies, became friends\\\" by pushing themselves to greater heights.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rankin\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"comrades\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2481}, {\"ngram\": \"allies\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"friends\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"greater heights\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What came from that was a bond, a brotherhood, a connection between two world class athletes on the highest stage of their particular event or sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bond\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2588}, {\"ngram\": \"a brotherhood\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"a connection\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2617}, {\"ngram\": \"two world class athletes\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest stage\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"their particular event\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2697}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Long was killed fighting for Nazi Germany in World War II, but the families of the Americn and German still remain in contact, bonded through their grandfathers' friendship, according to Rankin.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2739, \"end\": 2751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.5756330042137927, \"rank\": 0.6975126740186345, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9991847401321834, \"rank\": 0.0007478549267798427, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Long\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2714}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2767}, {\"ngram\": \"the families\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americn\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2835}, {\"ngram\": \"their grandfathers' friendship\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens' grandson recalls traveling to Munich for business and a colleague, upon finding out who his grandfather was, asked if he knew who Long was.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 3052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"score\": 0.9995287010093747, \"rank\": 0.0004705333846726458, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://d